as it like this with me?\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Walter looks to Henry. His lack of response confirms it wasn't. Something is wrong.\par Then, silence.\par Walter lowers his pipe. Faces the front door. Waiting. Standing in the painful silence.\par He can't take it anymore -- lunges forward -- bursts in the front door --\par Henry strains to see past his father. \par His pregnant MOTHER lies motionless on the kitchen table.\par A weary DOCTOR approaches Walter with trembling hands.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 Doctor\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 I'm sorry, Walter.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 He can barely pat Walter on the shoulder as he passes by.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 \par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Walter's emotions overwhelm him. He folds in on himself, dropping to his knees before his dead wife.\par Henry watches from the doorway. His eyes welling with tears.\par }{\pard\plain \qr \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s7\fi0\ri2020\li7920 Fade out:\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Fade in:}{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 \par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb480\f66\fs24\sl180\s2\fi0\ri1440\li2160 EXT. Mast farm - dAY\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Under grey skies. Walter hacks at the earth with a shovel. Stone-faced. Focused only on his task. Dig.\par }{\pard\plain \qr \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s7\fi0\ri2020\li7920 CuT TO:\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb480\f66\fs24\sl180\s2\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Later\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Walter and Henry stand before a fresh grave bearing two wooden crosses. There are no words.\par }{\pard\plain \qr \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s7\fi0\ri2020\li7920 FADE OUT:\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb480\f66\fs24\sl180\s2\fi0\ri1440\li2160 iNT. Mast HOUSE - walter's bedroom - mORNING\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Sunrise spills through an open window. A soft breeze tickles the curtains.\par Somewhere in the mess on the bed lies Walter. A farmer ought to be up by now. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \b\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 TITLE: Eight months later}{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 \par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 HENRY (o.S.)\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Pa!\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Walter groans.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 HENRY (o.S.)\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Pa, we're going to be late.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Walter swings his legs out of bed. An empty whiskey bottle falls to the floor. Not that he noticed.\par Walter's face hangs heavy. Tired. Unshaven.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb480\f66\fs24\sl180\s2\fi0\ri1440\li2160 EXT. Mast HOUSE - DAY\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 The fields look fallow. Henry drives their farm wagon, and their one horse, up to the front of the house.\par Henry's shirt is tucked in and his hair is combed. His version of Sunday's best when you can't afford more.\par Walter exits the house, tucking his shirt in as he goes.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 HENRY\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Come on!\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Walter climbs into the wagon at his own pace.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb480\f66\fs24\sl180\s2\fi0\ri1440\li2160 iNT. Modest frontier church - DAY\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 The church is shoulder-to-shoulder as PARISHIONERS sing }{\pard\plain \ql \ul\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 All Creatures Of Our God And King}{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 .\par Perched in the front pew and singing louder than anyone is LOUIS SUTTER, early 40's. His opulent clothes hinting at arrogance. There's no dirt under this man's nails.\par To Louis's sides are his wife ELIZABETH, late 30's, and daughters ANNA, 9, and MARY, 11.\par Mary takes her eyes off her hymnal just long enough to catch Henry staring at her from another pew, a few rows back. \par Henry doesn't look away. Just offers a soft smile that Mary returns.\par Walter sings from the doorway with the same lack of enthusiasm he's given the rest of the day.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb480\f66\fs24\sl180\s2\fi0\ri1440\li2160 EXT. Modest frontier church - DAY\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Parishioners vacate the church. Walter chats with a group of fellow FARMERS.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 grim farmer\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Heard he bought another one.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 woEFUL farmer\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Where?\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 grim farmer\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Sarpy county.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 Neighbor\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Sarpy... He's out to own the whole territory. Nebraska even.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 WaLTER\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Man's got means. What can you do?\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 Neighbor\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Tell you what I'd like to do--\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Louis exits the church, glad-handing everyone as he goes.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 Neighbor\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Look at that peacock. Like he's president or something.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Louis passes by. His steely gaze locks with Walter's.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 Neighbor\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Be a cold day in hell before he gets my farm.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Walter can't pull his uneasy eyes from Louis.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb480\f66\fs24\sl180\s2\fi0\ri1440\li2160 iNT. small town bank - DAY\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Walter sits across the desk from a BANK OFFICIAL who can't stop wringing his hands.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 BANK OFFICIAL\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 I'd really like to help. I really would...\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 WaLTER\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 I'm not asking for a hand-out, George. It's been a tough season. I just need more time.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 Bank official\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 You've already exceeded the grace period. Twice.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 WALTER\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 I know--\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 BANK OFFICIAL\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 You've accrued penalties that frankly it doesn't appear you're capable of recompensing.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 WALTER\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 I know--\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 BANK OFFICIAL\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 If you're unable to make payment by month's end you're going to default on your mortgage and the bank will be forced to foreclose. Do you understand what I'm saying? We'll take your farm, Walter.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 This hits Walter hard.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb480\f66\fs24\sl180\s2\fi0\ri1440\li2160 EXT. Mast FARM - DAY\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Walter stops his wagon in front of the house. A moment passes as he take stock of his situation.\par He grabs a whiskey bottle and knocks it back. Takes a long hard look at his farm.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 WaLTER\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Henry!\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 No response.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 WALTER\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Boy!\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Nothing. Where is he?\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb480\f66\fs24\sl180\s2\fi0\ri1440\li2160 eXT. prairie - DAy\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 A kite. Flying high over the prairie. Below there's laughter.\par Mary wrestles with the kite line. It's windy enough that the kite keeps pulling at her hands.\par She trades smiles with Henry.\par -- a gust of wind grabs the kite -- jerks Mary to her toes --\par Henry springs into action. Grabs her. \par Their weight too much, the kite line SNAPS and they fall to the ground in a heap.\par They're face-to-face. Smiles and awkwardness. If they were older this would be where they'd kiss. Instead --\par -- they look to the sky. Mary's kite floats away forever.\par Suddenly Mary bursts out laughing and leaps to her feet. \par Henry watches her dance to music only she can hear. Gliding across the prairie without a care in the world. Henry smiles.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb480\f66\fs24\sl180\s2\fi0\ri1440\li2160 EXT. Mast HOUSE - sunset\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Henry approaches the house with a contented smile. Until he gets close enough to see --\par Walter is on the porch. Smoking his pipe. On his way to drunk.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 WALTER\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Where you been?\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 HENRY\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Out.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Henry blasts past him. Letting the door slam after him.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 WALTER\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 You missed your chores!\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Walter doesn't go after him. Like always.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb480\f66\fs24\sl180\s2\fi0\ri1440\li2160 eXT. Neighbor farm - DAY\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Walter's wagon enters the long dusty lane to his neighbor's farm. \par As he nears the house he spots an unexpected sight: Neighbor packing his wagon.\par Neighbor is visibly upset.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 WALTER\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 What's going on here?\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 NEIGHBOR\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 I didn't have a choice. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Walter looks to the house where Louis is directing MEN. Walter realizes: Neighbor sold his farm.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 NEIGHBOR\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 I got a family to think about.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 WALTER\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 What did he offer?\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 NEIGHBOR\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Enough. He offered enough.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 WALTER\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Neighbor lifts his WIFE and TWO DAUGHTERS into the wagon. Then climbs in himself.\par Walter is incensed. Betrayed.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 WALTER\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 I never thought you'd be the sort to cut and run. Well go ahead. Scurry back to Kansas, you gutless cur. See if you can't get work making womens' dresses cuz you sure as hell ain't no granger.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Neighbor takes the abuse. He couldn't feel much worse anyway. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 NEIGHBOR\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 There's nothing here for me. Nothing for you either. Time to move on.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Neighbor flicks the reigns. His wagon ambles off.\par Walter can feel Louis's eyes on him. Staring at him with fixed interest. Walter meets his gaze. Two titans of will in a silent stand-off.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb480\f66\fs24\sl180\s2\fi0\ri1440\li2160 eXT. mast farm - dAY\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 The sun blazes overhead. Walter is in the field, struggling to run a plow behind his horse.\par Louis's carriage rustles down the farm lane. \par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb480\f66\fs24\sl180\s2\fi0\ri1440\li2160 EXT. masT HOUSE - momeNTS LATER\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Louis climbs from his carriage just as Henry rounds the house and freezes -- stunned to see him.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 Louis\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Afternoon, son. Is your father here?\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Henry doesn't answer. Intimidated on every level.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 LoUIS\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 I asked you a question. It's impolite not to answer. That is unless you're dumb. You're not dumb, are you, boy?\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Louis approaches Henry. Each step further illustrating how small Henry is to him.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 WALTER (o.S.)\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Go on inside, Henry.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Louis turns to see Walter only a few steps away.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 WALTER\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s5\fi-140\ri4320\li4320 (to Henry)\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Go on.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Henry runs inside.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 LOUIS\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Afternoon, Mr. Mast. My name is Louis--\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24