w behind.\par Walter can only watch as it jangles and digs, puncturing his land in a Morse code of destruction.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 WALTER\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 No!\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 The horse barrels right into his wife's grave. Destroying the cross. Ripping soil like an open wound.\par Walter clenches his jaw. Lets out a roar. He's had enough...\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb480\f66\fs24\sl180\s2\fi0\ri1440\li2160 eXT. suTTER HOUSE - DAY\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Henry and Mary hide behind a tree in her back yard.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 HENRY\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 There's a train tonight. Well have to go on the fly and hide in the cow crate so the bulls don't get us. When we get to Lincoln we'll find a flop. I'll get work in a factory. You'll have to work too.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Mary looks dismayed by his plan.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 MARY\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 I don't want to leave.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 HENRY\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 It's okay. I'm scared too. We'll be fine.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 MARY\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 That's easy for you to say you're not leaving anything behind.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Henry is stunned. She's never insulted him before.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 HENRY\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 It's the only way we can be together.\par }{\par