 it. Something's not right.\par Mary's the first to look up. Her eyes going wide. Mouth agape.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 MARY\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Daddy...\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Louis looks to the sky. The dread washing over his face too.\par Finally Walter pries his focus from Louis. Gazes to the heavens.\par The sky is alive in a swarm of locusts. Millions of them. Enough to block the sun, and every other inch of sky.\par Walter lowers his rifle in sheer awe.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 WALTER\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 My God.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Louis stumbles toward the house.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 LOUIS\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Inside! Everybody inside!\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Everyone rushes for the house as the swarm descends at them.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb480\f66\fs24\sl180\s2\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Int./ext. SUTTER HOUSE - front door - conTINUOUS\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Elizabeth pushes Mary inside. Louis pulls the screen door tight behind.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 ELIZABETH\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 What are you doing?\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Henry and Walter scramble for the porch. Swatting locusts as they go.\par Henry gets to the door first. He jerks at the handle but Louis holds it fast.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 HeNRY\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Let us in.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Henry jerks at the door to no avail.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 MARY\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Let him in.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 ELIZABETH\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Louis, please.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 The locusts are everywhere now. Engulfing the landscape. The ground turning to a living carpet of hungry insects.\par Walter finally makes it to the porch.\par Louis lets go of the door -- grabs his rifle from Elizabeth -- raises it in time to meet Walter's. Both men are face-to-face with each other's guns.\par Locusts crawl across Walter but he doesn't flinch. This could be his chance to kill Louis.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 HeNRY\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Mr. Sutter--\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 MARY\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 Daddy...\par }{\pard\plain \ql \caps\sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s4\fi0\ri1800\li5040 LOUIS\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s5\fi-140\ri4320\li4320 (to Walter)\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb0\f66\fs24\sl180\s6\fi0\ri3600\li3600 You're not getting in here with that rifle.\par }{\pard\plain \ql \sb240\f66\fs24\sl180\s3\fi0\ri1440\li2160 Walter stares into Louis's cold eyes. \par He can hear Henry screaming, struggling to wipe the locusts clean. They need to get inside fast.\par }}